        <item description="This letter creates a comparison between a traditional compressed air system, and one with intelligent monitoring capabilities.  It contains the most prominent cost drivers and supporting materials that capture the value of SCOUT. This analysis includes measurable costs such as labor, materials, and quantified counterproductive events.  Additional benefits of SCOUT also include the peace of mind that your system is operating at an optimal state.  If a variable is detected to be approaching the boundaries of a programmed scope, a warning is sent to appropriate personnel.  An alert is sent if a programmable variable is breached." />
